    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>What the desktop can do on this baseline</h2>
      <ul class="check-list">
        <li>Open and verify a local Research Workspace through structured application services.</li>
        <li>Preview and confirm workspace initialization, local Search import, and deterministic analysis.</li>
        <li>Display a verified deduplication review queue and record an authorized human decision after exact-effect confirmation.</li>
        <li>Conduct title/abstract Screening, correction, adjudication, and handoff through exact preview/confirm bindings.</li>
        <li>Run candidate-local Full Text intake and human review over immutable local evidence.</li>
        <li>Produce deterministic reports, Bundle v2 inventories, and append-only export-ledger records with round-trip verification.</li>
        <li>Create a manifest-verified local backup and restore exact bytes into a new workspace folder.</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="callout boundary">
        <strong>Not yet admitted on this baseline</strong>
        Protocol or criteria authoring, provider operation from the desktop, model calls, plugin execution, authentication, database/cloud state, and multi-user collaboration.
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>Validation and delivery posture</h2>
      <p>The repository uses protected-main validation on Windows and Linux. Core validation remains on Ubuntu; Windows builds the self-contained portable artifact twice, verifies its inventory, extracts it, and executes its local smoke without a repository or installed .NET runtime. Exact matching tags add checksums, SPDX SBOM, GitHub attestation, and prerelease publication. CodeQL and dependency review run independently.</p>
      <ul class="link-list">
        <li><a href="https://github.com/nexus-scholar-org/core-csharp/actions">GitHub Actions history</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/nexus-scholar-org/core-csharp/blob/main/.github/workflows/gate-01.yml">Main verification workflow</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/nexus-scholar-org/core-csharp/blob/main/docs/release/PACKAGES.md">Package topology and reproducibility</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/nexus-scholar-org/core-csharp/releases/tag/v0.1.0-alpha.2">Windows technical preview</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/nexus-scholar-org/core-csharp/blob/main/SECURITY.md">Security policy</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section">
      <h2>Claims deliberately not made</h2>
      <div class="feature-grid">
        <article class="feature"><h3>No production release</h3><p>The desktop is an unsigned technical preview. Packages are validation-only and unpublished; there is no supported installer or production operating claim.</p></article>
        <article class="feature"><h3>No connected platform</h3><p>No database, API, cloud synchronization, tenant isolation, or multi-user collaboration is claimed.</p></article>
        <article class="feature"><h3>No autonomous science</h3><p>Automation and model outputs cannot become final scientific decisions by themselves.</p></article>
        <article class="feature"><h3>Bounded network scope</h3><p>OpenAlex and Semantic Scholar Search are exact-host, opt-in outward adapters. There is no live Crossref or Full Text retrieval, scraping, paywall bypass, PDF parsing, OCR, or live citation provider.</p></article>
        <article class="feature"><h3>No plugin runtime</h3><p>Capability and manifest contracts exist; third-party execution and sandbox claims do not.</p></article>
        <article class="feature"><h3>No broad compatibility</h3><p>PHP classifications are case- and fixture-scoped. They are not a blanket compatibility promise.</p></article>
      </div>
    </section>
